1. **`write_and_read_data` function:**
   - Creates a `std::vector<uint8_t>` buffer
   - Uses `buffer_write_adaptor` to write input data after checking available space with `free()`
   - Uses `buffer_read_adaptor` to read data back after checking readable size with `size()`
   - Returns the read data

2. **`peek_data_without_advancing` function:**
   - Creates a non-const copy of the input buffer since `buffer_read_adaptor` requires non-const reference
   - Uses `copy()` method to peek at data without advancing read pointer
   - Uses `read_ptr()` to demonstrate getting the current read position
   - Uses `read()` method to actually consume the data (advance read pointer)
